FBIS4-62918 "drsov097_e_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Europarliament Ecologists Visit Defense Ministry Europarliament Ecologists Visit Defense Ministry MK1805112994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 18 May 94 p 2 MK1805112994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Russian BFN [Report by Vladimir Matyash under the "In Brief" rubric: "Common Language is One of Ecology"] [Text] Moscow -- A meeting took place in the Russian Federation Defense Ministry between Major General Sergey Grigorov, chief of the Russian Federation Defense Ministry, ecology and special protection funds directorate, and European Parliament deputies Christian Rousing and Freddy Blak. The visitors from Denmark saw for themselves how the storing and utilization of nuclear weapons and propulsion plants in the Army and the Navy is done by experienced specialists with the aid of the most up-to-date technical monitoring equipment. However, due to considerable cuts in nuclear arms and redeployment of missile units there is a lack of ecology specialists. The Europarliament deputies voiced readiness for cooperation in jointly training them.
